		<band height="180">
			<staticText>
				<reportElement positionType="Float" x="25" y="0" width="545" height="180" uuid="971f8424-c7b6-44ea-aa62-217dd77f3b6c"/>
				<textElement textAlignment="Justified" verticalAlignment="Middle" markup="html">
					<font size="12" pdfFontName="net/sf/jasperreports/fonts/dejavu/DejaVuSerif-Italic.ttf" isPdfEmbedded="true"/>
				</textElement>
				<text><![CDATA[In general, the blood ccfDNA can be influenced by inadequate blood collection procedures/storage/shipping conditions, plasma separation and ccfDNA isolation procedures. The post-collection release of genomic DNA from white blood cells can change the ccfDNA profile significantly. This can impact validity.                                        Using blood collection tubes containing ccfDNA profile stabilisers is therefore recommended, The tubes catalogue and Lot number should be documented.    If no ccfDNA-stabilised tubes are used, EDTA blood collection tubes should be preferred over other collection tubes. Induced clotting processes in serum tubes can lead to leucocytes lysis and should therefore be avoided. induced clotting process in serum tubes can lead to a leucocytes lysis causing release of DNA, thus changing the native ccfDNA profile. Use of serum tubes should be avoided.]]></text>
			</staticText>
		</band>
